  "text": "[34] A primary goal of the work by [CITATION_1] was to calculate the amount of water bound to the rock during alteration. In a model based on the Shergotty SNC meteorite, $8% of the final mineral assemblage (by weight) was water, implying that water/rock ratios >0.08 would be necessary to sustain hydrothermal circulation. Assuming the Shergotty composition is sufficiently generic to be applied to our own models, a W/R limit of 0.08 implies a minimum permeability of 10 À16 m 2 for a 150°C reaction in host rock surrounding a 2000 km 3 chamber (Table 1 ).",
